Japanese Sold Net 1187.1 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week

-- B y   T h e r e s a   B a r r a c l o u g h
-- 
2011-06-08T23:53:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-08/japanese-sold-net-1187-1-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
sellers of foreign bonds during the week ended June 3 according to
figures based on reports from designated major investors released by
the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors sold 1187.1 billion yen ($14.9 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, bought 98.7 billion yen in overseas stocks
and bought 17.8 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net sale of 1070.6 billion yen.  Foreign investors sold 260.8 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
bought 8.6 billion yen in stocks, and sold 685.8 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net sale 938
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
Theresa Barraclough in Tokyo at   tbarraclough@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  